{
  "stem": "18102.5",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And of course, they found out to their dismay that he was right and they were wrong when the arrests began.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "It wasn't until weeks later that suddenly a neighbor of ours who had a telephone-- that was a rare commodity among Jews in Poland.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "You had to be very wealthy to own the telephone-- got a telephone call, and came rushing to our house to ask my mother-- to tell her that my father was on the phone and wanted to talk with her.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And my mother, of course, ran off to get the call.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "When she came back, it was the first time she felt the mixture of relief and trepidation again, because my father was well and was alive.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "But now our trek of running began in real terms.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "My father had found out that Vilna, the city of Vilna, that it was always in a tug-of-war between Poland and Lithuania as to who owned Vilna, was going to be turned over to the Lithuanians by the Russians.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And therefore, Vilna would be a safe place for my father to reunite with his family if my mother and I would take the last immediate train out of Bialystock to Vilna and meet him there.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "Because there, he would be safe.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "The reason he didn't feel that he was safe under the Bolsheviks was that he was an outspoken anti-Communist.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "He was a member of the Bundists, which was a socialist movement, of course.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "But socialism and Communism were eons apart.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "And in his view, the Communists were not to be trusted any more than the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "And so he felt in Lithuania he would be free to return, that is, and reunite with us.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
